The `setRolloverSound` method in the DirectButton class manages sound playback when a button is hovered over. It checks if a rollover sound is defined; if so, it assigns this sound to play on hover events, otherwise, it clears any existing hover sounds. This method enhances user interaction by providing auditory feedback during state transitions.

def setRolloverSound(self):
        rolloverSound = self['rolloverSound']
        if rolloverSound:
            self.guiItem.setSound(DGG.ENTER + self.guiId, rolloverSound)
        else:
            self.guiItem.clearSound(DGG.ENTER + self.guiId)
